{{Infobox NRHP | name = Central Ohio Lunatic Asylum | nrhp_type = | image = Central Ohio Lunatic Asylum - cornerstone.jpg | caption = | location= [[Columbus, Ohio]] | coordinates = | locmapin = Ohio#USA | area = | built = | architect= | architecture= | added = | governing_body = | refnum=86000851 }} {{Infobox Hospital | Name = Columbus State Hospital | Org/Group = <!-- optional --> | Image = Columbus State Hospital c. 1880.jpg | Caption = Aerial view of Columbus State Hospital, {{circa}} 1880 | Logo = <!-- optional --> | Region = [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]] | State = [[Ohio]] | Country = US | Coordinates = <!-- optional; use template coord with 'display=inline,title' --> | HealthCare = Public | Type = | Speciality = [[Psychiatric hospital]] | Standards = <!-- optional if no national standards --> | Beds = | Founded = 1877 | Closed = 1980 | Website = }}
'''Columbus State Hospital''', also known as Ohio State Hospital for Insane, was a public psychiatric hospital in [[Columbus, Ohio]], established in 1877.<ref name=kb>{{cite web|url=http://www.kirkbridebuildings.com/buildings/columbus/|work=Kirkbride Buildings|title=Columbus State Hospital|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}</ref> The original hospital was constructed under the [[Kirkbride Plan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://library.osu.edu/blogs/mhcb/2011/09/26/ohio-state-hospital/|work=Ohio State University Library|title=Columbus State Hospital|date=September 26, 2011|accessdate=May 9, 2017}}</ref>
==History== The original hospital building, known as the Lunatic Asylum of Ohio, was completed in 1838.<ref name=kb/> In 1868, a fire destroyed the asylum, and it was rebuilt in the [[Kirkbride Plan|Kirkbride]] style in 1877.<ref name=kb/> The hospital was closed in 1980, and demolished between 1991 and 1996.<ref name=kb/>
