{{Infobox University | name = Iranian Mental Health Research Network | native_name = شبكه تحقيقات سلامت روان ايران | motto = | established = May 2006 | type = [[Public university|Public]] | city = [[Tehran]] | state = [[Tehran province|Tehran]] | country = [[Iran]] | president = [[Jafar Bolhari]] | undergrad = | postgrad = | faculty = | enrollment = | website = {{URL|http://www.mhrn.net/}} }} '''Iranian Mental Health Research Network''' '''(MHRN)''' ({{lang-fa|شبكه تحقيقات سلامت روان}}) is a network of some related [[research]] centers founded in 2006 in [[Iran]]. The network is supervised by the Iranian Deputy of Research and Technology of the Ministry of Health. Currently it includes ten centers active in the field of [[mental health]] research. The network aims to promote high quality research in this field, especially applied research and Health System Research. Developing the [[databases]] of published articles in [[Persian language|Persian]] (Iranpsych) and other useful databases for Iranian researchers (including researchers and psychological assessment tools) is one of the primary goals of the network. Director of the Iranian MHRN is Dr [[Jafar Bolhari]], a psychiatrist and current director of [http://www.iums.ac.ir/index.php?sid=13&slc_lang=en Tehran Psychiatric Institute].
