{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Gay & Lesbian Mental Health | cover = jglmh cover.gif | abbreviation = J. Gay Lesbian Ment. Health | formernames = Journal of Gay & Lesbian Psychotherapy | discipline = [[Psychiatry]] | editor = [[Mary E. Barber]], Alan Schwartz | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | history = 1988-present | frequency = Quarterly | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.informaworld.com/smpp/title~content=t792304010 | link1 = http://www.informaworld.com/smpp/title~db=all~content=t792304010~tab=issueslist | link1-name = Online access | ISSN = 1935-9705 | eISSN = 1935-9713 | LCCN = 2007214197 | OCLC = 83831862 }} The '''''Journal of Gay & Lesbian Mental Health''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[medical journal]] published by [[Routledge]]. It is the official journal for the [[Association of Gay and Lesbian Psychiatrists]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Philip Bialer and Chris Mcintosh. Former editors include [[Mary E. Barber]] ([[Columbia College of Physicians and Surgeons]]), Alan Schwartz ([[William Alanson White Institute]]), and Jack Drescher The journal was established in 1988 as the ''Journal of Gay & Lesbian Psychotherapy'', before obtaining its current title in 2007. It covers [[LGBT]] [[mental health]] with a focus on clinical issues. The journal is abstracted and indexed in: [[PsychInfo]], LGBT Life, [[SOCIndex]], [[Academic Search Premier]], [[Family Index Abstracts]], [[Studies in Women & Gender Abstracts]], and Gender Watch-Softline.
