'''Kerreen M Reiger''' (born 1946) is an [[Australian]] academic, sociologist and author.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.womenaustralia.info/leaders/biogs/WLE0725b.htm|title=Reiger, Kerreen M - Woman - The Encyclopedia of Women and Leadership in Twentieth-Century Australia|last=Harrison|first=Sharon|date=|website=www.womenaustralia.info|language=en-gb|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref> She lives in [[Melbourne]] and teaches [[sociology]] at [[La Trobe University]].  She has a special interest in family, motherhood and [[childbirth]]<ref>[http://www.smh.com.au/articles/2004/05/14/1084289895453.html?from=storyrhs Baby kissing]</ref> and was one of the founders of the activist group [[Maternity Coalition]].

